---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'Best AI Website Builders for Ecommerce (2025)';
const description = 'Which AI builders can actually run an online store? I tested ecommerce features across all builders. 10Web + WooCommerce wins.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">CATEGORY</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Best AI Website Builders for Ecommerce</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
        Selling online? Most AI builders can't handle real ecommerce. Here's what works.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Quick Ranking</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>10Web + WooCommerce:</strong> Full ecommerce, unlimited products, plugins for everything</li>
        <li><strong>Squarespace:</strong> Built-in ecommerce, easy to use, limited scalability</li>
        <li><strong>Webflow:</strong> Powerful ecommerce, expensive, designer-focused</li>
        <li><strong>Wix:</strong> Basic ecommerce, fine for small stores</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">10Web + WooCommerce - The Clear Winner</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Why WooCommerce Wins</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            WooCommerce powers 30% of all online stores for a reason. It can handle:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 space-y-1">
            <li>Unlimited products and variants</li>
            <li>100+ payment gateways</li>
            <li>Advanced shipping options</li>
            <li>Inventory management</li>
            <li>Tax calculation</li>
            <li>Subscription sales</li>
            <li>Booking systems</li>
            <li>And 50,000+ extensions for everything else</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">The 10Web Advantage</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            10Web gives you WooCommerce power WITH AI generation. You get the ease of AI setup + unlimited ecommerce capabilities.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What About Shopify?</h2>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
          <strong>Important:</strong> Shopify doesn't have AI generation. You build manually or use themes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <strong>Shopify vs 10Web + WooCommerce:</strong>
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Shopify:</strong> Easier for beginners, more expensive, less flexible, monthly fees add up</li>
        <li><strong>10Web + WooCommerce:</strong> Steeper learning curve, more powerful, cheaper long-term, unlimited flexibility</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
        <strong>Recommendation:</strong> For most ecommerce sites, 10Web + WooCommerce offers better value and capabilities than Shopify.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Ecommerce Reality Check</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <strong>Most AI builders CAN'T do real ecommerce.</strong>
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Durable, Framer, Dorik, Hostinger AI - these are fine for basic sites but terrible for serious online stores.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>If ecommerce is important:</strong> Choose 10Web, Squarespace, or Webflow. Don't waste time with limited ecommerce solutions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Which Ecommerce Builder for You?</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Selling 10-100 products:</strong> Squarespace is easiest</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Selling 100+ products:</strong> 10Web + WooCommerce</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Complex products (variants, subscriptions):</strong> 10Web + WooCommerce</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Design-focused brand:</strong> Webflow (expensive but beautiful)</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Digital downloads only:</strong> Any builder + Gumroad or SendOwl integration</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates['10web'].affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates['10web'].commission}
        label="Try 10Web for Ecommerce"
        className="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
